    feat: add Google Calendar MCP server
    
    Register @cocal/google-calendar-mcp as a dedicated calendar MCP, mount
    ~/.calendar-mcp/ into the container, and allow mcp__calendar__* tools.
    Decouples calendar access from the Gmail MCP, which was suffering scope
    strips from its periodic re-auth.
    
    GOOGLE_OAUTH_CREDENTIALS and GOOGLE_CALENDAR_MCP_TOKEN_PATH env vars pin
    both files inside the bind mount so refreshed tokens persist across
    container restarts.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

